{"lemma":"خاطِفِي","slug":"خاطِفِي","root":"خ.ط.ف","root_slug":"خ-ط-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ط-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11026"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%90%D9%81%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11026","headword_ar":"خَاطِفٌ","root":"xTf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of 1,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seizing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuT~aAfN","text_ar":"خُطَّافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaATifu","text_ar":"الخَاطِفُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wolf;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K;) because he seizes, or carries off by force, his prey. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaATifu Zil~ihi","text_ar":"خَاطِفُ ظِلِّهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,) said by Ibn-Selemeh to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aforaAfu","text_ar":"الرَّفْرَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, [so in three copies, not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqoraAq","text_ar":"رَقْرَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in Freytag's Lex.,] TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that sees its shadow, and thinks it to be a bird;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it sees its shadow in the water, it advances to it to seize it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thinking it to be a prey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayaAlN","text_ar":"خَيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the birds of the deserts, and is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thus called because of the swiftness with which it pounces down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the back; white in the belly; long in the wings, and short in the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lEb","text_ar":"لعب"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaAEibu Zil~ihi","text_ar":"مُلَاعِبُ ظِلِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S and Msb in that art.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroqN xaATifN","text_ar":"بَرْقٌ خَاطِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lightning that takes away the sight."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, * TA. *) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomN xaATifN","text_ar":"سَهْمٌ خَاطِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arrow that falls upon the ground, and then glides along upon the ground to the butt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of aim;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though snatching something from the ground: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xawaATifu","text_ar":"خَوَاطِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 573:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xawaATifu","text_ar":"خَوَاطِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies arrows"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that miss;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxoTifaAtN","text_ar":"مُخْطِفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","K","L","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}